text: Tureberg is a neighbourhood in Sollentuna Municipality, Stockholm County, Sweden. In 2011, 15,560 people lived there. It is a Stockholm suburb and houses the local government seat for the municipality as well as a large shopping mall and a Stockholm commuter rail station. Tureberg has also evolved as a law enforcement center for the northern part of metropolitan Stockholm, with police station, court house, prosecutor's office, and a jail,http://www.kriminalvarden.se/sv/Hakte/Vara- hakten/Sollentuna/accessdate=2013-03-28 all in buildings built in the 1980s and onwards. The present courthouse was inaugurated in 2010. ==References== Category:Settlements in Stockholm County
